The evidence with the title 'Counting the Cost Of Texas Health Care ' says Health care spending represents nearly half of the state budget. In fiscal 2015, Texas spent $ 42.9 billion on health care, or 43.1 percent of all its appropriations from  ... Medicaid , a federal program jointly financed by the federal and state  ... . Chronic disease is responsible for nearly two - thirds of all deaths in Texas each year. 
